Find a default input file safely.

Priority:
1) Exactly one supported file inside a dedicated 'whisper_input' folder.
2) Otherwise, stop and ask the user to provide --input.

This function does NOT scan the Desktop, Spyder folder or current directory.
©r`   u4   âœ… Auto-detected input file from dedicated folder: a–  No input file was provided and no safe default input file was found.

Recommended Spyder workflow:
1) Create a folder called 'whisper_input' on your Desktop or OneDrive Desktop.
2) Put exactly ONE supported audio/video file inside it.
3) Run the script from Spyder.

Alternative workflow:
Run the script from Anaconda Prompt with:
python transcribe.py --input "C:\path\to\audio.m4a"

